comments: I have taken several of her graduate and undergraduate course. I find her to be one of the most unbiased open professors. She wants students to open their minds to seeing things in a different light and challenges students. She is a lovely person as well as a great teacher.

This class was interesting and helpful. The teacher is great, very knowledgeable in this subject and very helpful. Guides you to the test but doesn\'t give it away. You have to work, but that\'s how you learn. I\'d take her again.

I found the class very worthwhile. The teacher makes things clear with practical application and steers you in the right direction on what to study and know for tests, but be sure you do know that material! I would certainly take her again and recommend her to any serious students.
I felt she was very biased and if you do not believe just as she does she will grade against you. If you don\'t have to take this class don\'t take it, waste of your time.
She\'s wonderful! One of the best teachers at Wilmington College. I really enjoyed this class.
Wonderful instructor and a first class lady. Her presentation of material is clear cut. Lively discussions. Always willing to help. She is not a push over. One of the best Wilmington College has.

Ethnic Minorities, Bibilical Studies. The thing I enjoy about her most is her way of teaching without interjecting personal opinion. She encourages class participation and is a great facilitator. I went into the class feeling confident that I was well versed in the subject matter, but I found that I learned more than I expected.TAKE HER CLASS!
Such a sweet woman. Teaches you a lot and is so helpful.

Enthic Minorities, and also Biblical Studies classes. She covers key points and gives you all testable areas, so if you read, take notes, and pay attention, you will be fine. I highly recommend this teacher. Don\'t put off papers, they are about 7 pages, but on very intersting topics. GREAT Teacher!
